Flight operations were conducted on November 17, 2017 onboard a Boeing 727-200F aircraft (G-Force One®, Zero Gravity Corporation). Four sets of parabolas were performed with 5, 6, 4, and 5 parabolas respectively (Fig. 1a). The first set targeted, in order, Mars g, Mars g, Lunar g, 0 g, and 0 g (Fig. 1b). All other parabolas targeted 0 g. The flight profile was segmented into periods of “transition”, “parabola”, “hypergravity”, and “other” (typically, gentle climb, descent, straight and level flight, or standard rate turns) on the basis of accelerometer measurements4. Sequencing was also performed on the ground prior to the flight as a control.Fig. 1Single molecule sequencing during parabolic flight.
